"(recommended setting). If it is larger than the interval, data overlap "
"will occur (effective when there is little data. However, since some of "
"the same data is evaluated, there is a concern that changes may become "
"slow). If the value is smaller than the interval, data will not overlap "
"and some data will not be evaluated (effective when there is a large "
"number of data. However, not recommended as some data will not be "
"evaluated). \n"
"e.g.) 1 week = 168h, 30 days = 720h, a half year = 4320h, one year = 8760h"

